description: Chad Chronister, President-elect Donald Trump's pick to lead the Drug Enforcement Administration, said Tuesday that he would withdraw his name from consideration for the post.

description: President-elect Donald Trump’s pick to lead the Defense Department, Pete Hegseth, is in peril over allegations concerning drinking and his treatment of women.

description: Rep. Sean Casten is forcing a floor vote to require the House Ethics Committee to release a report on its investigation into former Rep. Matt Gaetz.

description: A search and rescue effort was underway in Pennsylvania on Tuesday after a grandmother searching for her cat appears to have plunged into a sinkhole that authorities said was at least 30 feet deep.

description: U.S. officials update reporters on it’s investigation into a massive and ongoing Chinese hack of multiple U.S. telecom companies. NBC News Justice and Intelligence Correspondent Ken Dilanian reports on how government officials are grappling with the breach.

description: A small asteroid sped toward Earth before burning out above far northeastern Russia on Tuesday night, sparking a natural light show for residents in that remote corner of the planet, officials said.

description: An 8-year-old boy has died after a statue fell on him outside the luxury Arizona Biltmore hotel, the Phoenix Police Department said.

description: A good Samaritan who went outside to grab a delivery found two infant girls who were dumped in a ditch near his Indiana home after the car they were in was stolen.

description: A Central California woman died from rabies after she was bitten by a bat, officials said Tuesday, in the first fatality from the saliva-passed disease in her county in more than 30 years.

description: An Indian American man recorded a woman’s verbal attack against him and his family after they arrived at Los Angeles International Airport and boarded a shuttle bus. Pervez Taufiq said the woman was allegedly yelling at his child. NBC News cannot confirm what occurred before the video recording.

description: Large drones have been hovering in formation over northern New Jersey, officials said Monday, leading to "unnerved" residents wondering what's behind these bright, unidentified flying objects appearing almost every night in the sky.

description: Georgia’s longest-running criminal trial ended Tuesday with not guilty verdicts on all charges except for one for two remaining co-defendants in a sprawling racketeering case that had included rap superstar Young Thug.

description: Newly released video shows a woman who snuck onto a flight from New York to Paris last week being removed from a returning flight back to the United States after she started screaming.

description: A new Arctic blast is set to dump more snow onto the Great Lakes and the Northeast, as winter weather caused transport chaos and left thousands stranded.

description: Newly released video shows the stowaway who successfully managed to bypass security at JFK airport to board a Delta flight to Paris, being removed from a return flight after causing a disturbance. NBC’s Stephanie Gosk reports for TODAY.

description: Netflix’s documentary series “Cold Case: Who Killed JonBenét Ramsey” that re-examines the 1996 killing of the 6-year-old is raising new hope among investigators to bring closure. Boulder police says the case could have been handled better and hopes the docuseries will generate more tips from the public decades later. NBC’s Liz Kreutz reports for TODAY and NBC’s Danny Cevallos breaks down what the future of the case could look like.
title: Police address renewed interest in JonBenét Ramsey case

description: Israel and Hezbollah traded new attacks Monday, stoking concerns their fragile cease-fire could unravel less than one week after going into effect, but the Biden administration insists the deal is holding despite the violence. Meanwhile, President-elect Trump says “there will be all hell to pay” if hostages held by Hamas are not released by the time he takes office. NBC’s Matt Bradley reports for TODAY.
title: Israel-Hezbollah cease-fire threatened after barrage of attacks

description: Donald Trump could use Joe Biden’s pardon of Hunter Biden for his own gain, some worry.
